SIMPLE: explain
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Explain
<hw>Ex*plain"</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧ks*pl⟦amac⟧n")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Explained</conjf><pr>(⟦ecr⟧ks*pl⟦amac⟧nd")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Explaining</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>explandare</ets> to flatten, spread out, explain; <ets>ex</ets> out
+ <ets>plandare</ets> to make level or plain, <ets>planus</ets> plain:
cf. OF. <ets>esplaner</ets>, <ets>explaner</ets>. See
<er>Plain</er>,<pos>a.</pos>, and cf. <er>Esplanade</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To flatten; to spread out; to unfold; to expand.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The horse-chestnut is . . . ready to <qex>explain</qex> its
leaf.</q> <rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make plain, manifest, or intelligible; to clear
of obscurity; to expound; to unfold and illustrate the meaning of;
<as>as, to <ex>explain</ex> a chapter of the Bible</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Commentators to <qex>explain</qex> the difficult passages to
you.</q> <rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To explain away</b></col>, <cd>to get rid of by
explanation.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧Those <xex>explain</xex> the meaning quite
<xex>away</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To expound; interpret; elucidate; clear
up.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Explain</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Explain
<hw>Ex*plain"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To give an
explanation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Explainable</ent>⟦br⟧
